  "prompt": "How can the government policy of demonetization help the government to recover the black money?",
  "response": "Demonetization can help the government recover black money through several mechanisms:\n\n1. Cash Declaration\n- Forcing people to deposit undeclared cash in banks\n- Requiring individuals to explain the source of large cash holdings\n- Imposing penalties for unexplained wealth\n\n2. Tracking Financial Transactions\n- Creating digital transaction trails\n- Enabling better monitoring of financial activities\n- Reducing cash-based transactions that often hide black money\n\n3. Reducing Cash Circulation\n- Limiting the volume of unaccounted cash in the economy\n- Encouraging digital and transparent financial transactions\n- Making it difficult to store large amounts of undeclared cash\n\n4. Tax Compliance\n- Increasing transparency in financial systems\n- Compelling individuals to report income more accurately\n- Identifying tax evaders through bank deposits\n\n5. Formal Banking Integration\n- Bringing more people into the formal banking system\n- Creating digital financial records\n- Making income and wealth more traceable\n\n6. Invalidating Existing Currency\n- Rendering existing high-denomination notes worthless\n- Forcing holders of black money to either deposit or lose their unaccounted wealth\n- Creating a disincentive for accumulating large cash reserves\n\n7. Enhanced Financial Surveillance\n- Implementing stricter Know Your Customer (KYC) norms\n- Using advanced data analytics to identify suspicious transactions\n- Improving information exchange between financial institutions\n\nThese strategies aim to reduce black money circulation and promote financial transparency.",
